A South African National Defence Force (SANDF) member died and 17 others were injured in a road accident between Malelane and Macadamia on Hectorspruit Road in Mpumalanga, the SANDF said.
In a statement, the SANDF said the accident happened at around 3.30pm on Tuesday.
“The accident took place when the members of 4 South African Infantry Battalion (4 SAI BN) were travelling in a bus on route from Nelspruit to Macadamia. One member died on the scene and 17 others incurred minor injuries,” SANDF said.
“They were taken to Tonga Hospital. The name of the deceased will be released once the next-of-kin have been informed.”
SANDF said that a board of inquiry would be instituted to determine the cause of the accident.
Defence and Military Veterans Minister, Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula; Secretary for Defence, Dr Sam Gulube; and the Chief of the SANDF, General Solly Shoke expressed their heartfelt condolences to the family, friends and loved ones of the deceased member.
“The top leadership of the SANDF also wishes a speedy recovery to those injured.”
– African News Agency (ANA)


